<table width="258" cellpadding="12" cellspacing="0" align="right" border="2" hspace="8" bordercolor="006699" bgcolor="#FFCC66"><tr><td>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#990000"><b>What else to read</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Elizabeth Schulte analyzed John Edwards for <i>Socialist Worker </i>when John Kerry chose him for his running mate in 2004 in an article called <a href="http://www.socialistworker.org/2004-2/507/507_09_Edwards.shtml" target="_blank">"The John-John team."</a><p>
For a look back at the Democrats during the 2004 presidential election, see <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FDimes-Worth-Difference-Beyond-Counterpunch%2Fdp%2F1904859038%2Fsr%3D8-6%2Fqid%3D1171853924%3Fie%3DUTF8%26amp%3Bs%3Dbooks&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">Dime's Worth of Difference: Beyond the Politics of Lesser of Two Evils</a>, </i>by <i>CounterPunch </i>editors Alexander Cockburn and Jeffrey St. Clair, and Joshua Frank's <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FLeft-Out-Liberals-Helped-Reelect%2Fdp%2F1567513107%3Fie%3DUTF8%26s%3Dbooks%26qid%3D1173235534%26sr%3D8-1&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" target="_blank">Left Out!: How Liberals Helped Reelect George W. Bush</a></i>.<p>
For a more general socialist analysis of the Democrats, you can download an ISO Web book by Lance Selfa, <i><a href="http://www.internationalsocialist.org/resources.html" target="_blank">The Democratic Party and the Politics of Lesser Evilism</a></i>.
